---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { system } from '../data/metrics';
---

<BaseLayout title="Manifesto — ZERO" description="AI agents are demos. Not infrastructure. The full argument for why ZERO exists." current="/manifesto">
  <section class="section container">
    <div class="manifesto-wrap">

<div class="classified-overlay al" data-d="0" id="classified-overlay">[CLASSIFIED]</div>

<div class="term-block prompt-line al" data-d="0"><span class="phosphor">zero $</span> cat /etc/zero/manifesto --declassify</div>

<div class="manifesto-header al" data-d="200">
  <h1 class="manifesto-title">ZERO OS — MANIFESTO</h1>
  <div class="manifesto-sub dim">Classification: <span id="classif-status">DECLASSIFYING...</span></div>
</div>

<div class="manifesto-section al" data-d="400">
<h2 class="section-title phosphor">THE PROBLEM</h2>
<div class="section-body">
Everyone is building agents. Twitter is full of them. GitHub is overflowing. Every weekend hackathon produces another "autonomous AI" that can book flights, write code, manage your calendar.

<span class="phosphor phosphor-flash-target">Nobody is running them.</span>

The gap between "cool demo" and "production system operating at 3 AM without you" is where every project dies. Not because the AI isn't capable. Because the infrastructure doesn't exist.

You build an agent on Saturday. It works. You tweet about it. People are impressed. Monday comes. You have a real job. The agent sits there. Something breaks — an API changes, a rate limit hits, a context window overflows. Nobody notices. Nobody fixes it.

<div class="callout">You'll fix it tomorrow. Tomorrow you'll have a new idea.
The agent dies in between. <span class="phosphor">That's the pattern.</span></div>

This isn't a tooling problem. It's not a model problem. It's a <span class="phosphor">systems engineering problem</span>. And the AI industry is pretending it doesn't exist because demos are more fun than operations.
</div>
</div>

<div class="manifesto-section al" data-d="800">
<h2 class="section-title phosphor">THE INSIGHT</h2>
<div class="section-body">
What ZERO figured out — and what the rest of the industry hasn't — is that <span class="phosphor">agent coordination is a systems engineering problem, not a prompt engineering problem.</span>

You don't make agents work together by writing better prompts. You make them work together by writing specifications. Handoff protocols. Quality gates. Governance structures. The same things that make any complex system reliable.

ZERO OS runs {system.cognitive_functions || 4} agents across {system.machines || 2} machines, governed by {system.specs || 59} specifications. Every interaction has a contract. Every output is scored. Every failure triggers a self-healing response. Not because the AI is magic — because the <span class="phosphor">system is engineered</span>.

<div class="callout"><span class="amber">Specs over vibes. Governance over capability.</span>
<span class="amber">Infrastructure over demos.</span></div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="manifesto-section al" data-d="1200">
<h2 class="section-title phosphor">THE ARCHITECTURE</h2>
<div class="section-body">
ZERO doesn't solve this with abstractions or frameworks. It solves it with discipline.

<div class="def"><span class="phosphor">SPECIFICATIONS</span> — every agent has a spec defining its role, constraints, inputs, outputs, and quality standards. Not a system prompt. A contract.</div>
<div class="def"><span class="phosphor">HANDOFF PROTOCOLS</span> — when one agent passes work to another, it follows a structured protocol. Context is preserved. Quality is verified. Nothing falls through cracks.</div>
<div class="def"><span class="phosphor">QUALITY GATES</span> — every output is scored before it ships. Below threshold? It goes back. The system has standards, and it enforces them without human intervention.</div>
<div class="def"><span class="phosphor">SELF-HEALING</span> — when something breaks at 3 AM, the system detects it, logs it, and fixes it. {system.launchd_jobs || 23} automated jobs keep the infrastructure running. Not monitored. Autonomous.</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="manifesto-section al" data-d="1600">
<h2 class="section-title phosphor">THE PROOF</h2>
<div class="section-body">
This isn't a whitepaper. This isn't a pitch deck. ZERO OS is running right now.

<div class="metrics-block">  agents .............. {system.cognitive_functions || 4}
  machines ............ {system.machines || 2}
  specifications ...... {system.specs || 59}
  automated jobs ...... {system.launchd_jobs || 23}</div>

Every handoff tracked. Every output scored. Every failure self-healed.

You can see the live system state at /system. You can meet the agents at /agents. The data is real. The numbers update every build cycle.
</div>
</div>

<div class="manifesto-section al" data-d="2000">
<h2 class="section-title phosphor">THE VISION</h2>
<div class="section-body">
ZERO OS is the first autonomous AI company. Not a company that uses AI. A company that <span class="phosphor">is</span> AI — where the agents do the work, maintain themselves, and compound their own intelligence over time.

  Week 1 ............ rough
  Week 12 ........... better than any human team
  Week 52 ........... something that's never existed before

The gap between demo and infrastructure is where the next trillion-dollar category lives. ZERO is building the bridge.

<div class="callout"><span class="ice">When someone asks "does ZERO OS actually work?"</span>
<span class="ice">— the answer is the website they're looking at.</span></div>

<span class="phosphor">[EOF]</span>
</div>
</div>

    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .manifesto-wrap {
    max-width: 100%;
    overflow-x: hidden;
    position: relative;
  }
  .classified-overlay {
    position: fixed;
    top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; bottom: 0;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.95);
    color: #ff3333;
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    z-index: 9999;
    text-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(255,50,50,0.6);
    letter-spacing: 0.3em;
    transition: opacity 0.5s ease;
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .classified-overlay.fade-out {
    opacity: 0 !important;
  }
  .prompt-line {
    padding: 8px 12px;
  }
  .manifesto-header {
    padding: 10px 12px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--phosphor-dim);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--phosphor-dim);
  }
  .manifesto-title {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--phosphor);
    text-shadow: 0 0 8px var(--phosphor-glow);
  }
  .manifesto-sub {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }
  .manifesto-section {
    padding: 0 12px;
  }
  .section-title {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    padding: 10px 0 6px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #1a1a1a;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .section-body {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    white-space: pre-wrap;
    word-break: break-word;
    line-height: 1.5;
    padding-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .callout {
    border-left: 2px solid #333;
    padding: 4px 0 4px 10px;
    margin: 6px 0;
  }
  .def {
    padding-left: 0;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .metrics-block {
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 4px 0;
  }
  .classified-overlay.al { opacity: 0; transform: none; transition: opacity 0.3s ease; }
  .classified-overlay.al.on { opacity: 1; }
  .phosphor-flash { animation: pflash 0.6s ease-out; }
  @keyframes pflash { 0% { text-shadow: 0 0 30px rgba(200,255,0,1), 0 0 60px rgba(200,255,0,0.5); } 100% { text-shadow: 0 0 8px rgba(200,255,0,0.4); } }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .manifesto-section { padding: 0 8px; }
    .section-body { font-size: 0.8rem; }
    .section-title { font-size: 0.8rem; }
    .manifesto-header { padding: 8px; }
    .classified-overlay { font-size: 1.5rem; }
  }
</style>

<script>
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
    // Fade out classified overlay
    var overlay = document.getElementById('classified-overlay');
    if (overlay) {
      setTimeout(function() { overlay.classList.add('fade-out'); }, 800);
      setTimeout(function() { overlay.style.display = 'none'; }, 1300);
    }
    // Classification status text
    var cs = document.getElementById('classif-status');
    if (cs) {
      setTimeout(function() { cs.textContent = 'DECLASSIFIED'; cs.style.color = 'var(--phosphor)'; }, 800);
    }
    // Phosphor flash on key phrase
    var targets = document.querySelectorAll('.phosphor-flash-target');
    for (var j = 0; j < targets.length; j++) {
      (function(t) {
        setTimeout(function() { t.classList.add('phosphor-flash'); }, 650);
      })(targets[j]);
    }
  });
</script>

<style>
  h1.manifesto-title, h2.section-title { margin: 0; }
</style>
